{"build_type":"library","description":"As-completed worker result publish: atomically claims a result slot, writes the JSON result into the result array, bumps the doorbell permit count and seq, and rings the collector doorbell via wake-doorbell-waiter-terminating-calling-thread; the clone trampoline then exits the thread. The result slot index is masked to the ring capacity (idx & 4095) so an unbounded as-completed producer wraps within the 4096-slot result array instead of writing out of bounds. Slice 4.4a: the result cstring is first copied into a standalone pool region (copy-cstring-into-standalone-pool-region) so it survives this worker's arena being reaped after the thread exits; the flat pointer is what lands in the result array.","module_name":"publish-worker-result-json-waking-collector-terminating-thread","package_name":"publish-worker-result-json-waking-collector-terminating-thread","function_definitions":{"publish-worker-result-json-waking-collector-terminating-thread":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"context","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"result","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"two","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"three","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":3},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"sixteen","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":16},{"instruction_type":"array_read","dest":"result_base","base":"context","index":"one","scale":8},{"instruction_type":"variable